ibbean-international/", "experiences/3/companyName": "Royal Caribbean International", "experiences/3/companySize": "10001-0", "experiences/3/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:3840996", "experiences/3/companyWebsite": "http://www.royalcaribbean.com", "experiences/3/employmentType": "Full-time", "experiences/3/jobDescription": "Food & Beverage Director for the World's largest cruise line operating 24 ships known for being the largest and boldest vessels on 6 continents. \nRoyal Caribbean International is synonymous for driving innovation at sea and constantly redefining cruise holiday experiences. \nOnboard Food & Beverage operations can include up to 20 restaurants and 20 bars depending on the class of ships. Concepts ranging from 3-deck main dining rooms, the iconic Windjammer buffet; and specialty dining such as Italian, Steakhouse, Japanese Hibachi and Sushi, Teppanyaki, Hot Pot, Sichuan, celebrity chef restaurant, Mexican, grab-and-go outlets; as well as exclusive dining areas for high-tier loyalty guests. \nResponsibilities revolve around driving food and beverage product and service quality, uncompromising guest satisfaction, revenues and team members engagement through a multinational Team.", "experiences/3/jobEndedOn": "7-2022", "experiences/3/jobLocationCountry": "US", "experiences/3/jobStartedOn": "2-2020", "experiences/3/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/3/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQEoOeKR8B-1Kg/company-logo_400_400/company-logo_400_400/0/1726070073702/royal_caribbean_international_logo?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=5yTXMcuMbFX-1CWupctMf1ev5iO2zpQyvJIwkuxh9F4", "experiences/3/title": "Director Of Food And Beverage", "experiences/4/companyName": "Tasty Thai Food Adventures", "experiences/4/jobDescription": "Identified market gaps and co-created a food tour company for inbound tourists; showcasing the best street food areas of Bangkok and surroundings; taking guests to markets, reputable street food areas, floating and night markets. Prepared all business and marketing plans, then obtained all necessary licenses to operate. The Explore, Taste, & Connect concept helped to sustain the Thai street food culture by helping local artisans preserve their culinary and cultural heritage through responsible tourism and operating our business in a way to minimize environmental impact, support the local community and contribute to the local economy. Tours were created to provide memorable experiences for guests as they Explored the best areas with a rich food culture and historical interests, away from commercial areas and tourist traps. The carefully curated stops allowed them to Taste as the locals do and digest the rich history of the foods and drinks they savored during their tours, allowing them to Connect with the local community and times past.", "experiences/4/jobEndedOn": "11-2018", "experiences/4/jobLocation": "Bangkok Metropolitan Area, Thailand", "experiences/4/jobStartedOn": "9-2017", "experiences/4/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/4/title": "Co-founder and Co-proprietor", "experiences/5/companyName": "Sands China Limited", "experiences/5/jobDescription": "Responsible for the entire Food and Beverage operation in a 5-star-deluxe casino resort. Directed all aspects of the service, beverage and culinary operation of 5 restaurants, entertainment lounge, and casino beverage services; as well as banquet operations, in-room dining and VIP club; with 29% average daily capture rate in the restaurants. Fine-dining outlets included 80-seats multiple-award winning and Best Steakhouse in Hong Kong-Macau COPA Steakhouse, and the signature fine-dining-Chinese 200-seats restaurant Golden Court.  Mass-volume outlets consisted of Las-Vegas-style 250-seats 888 Buffet, 888 Food Court with regional Asian and International cuisines (Cantonese, Northern Chinese, Sichuanese, Macanese, Thai, Japanese, Korean, coffee shop, and a Teppanyaki); and 24-hours Chinese noodle house Moonlight Market serving over 2,500 covers per day. Responsible for a team of 600 employees through 6 direct reports across administration, service, culinary and stewarding operations. Improved value propositions and drove profitable food and beverage programs resulting in record-breaking profit margins and leading multiple organization financial benchmarks. Planned, obtained capital and remodeled most F&B outlets. Implemented new projects such as Sweetspot Pastry shop, new wall of digital screens with menus and food imagery to increase outlets visibility and drive guest impulse buying; built new stylish fish tanks in Golden Court, increasing revenues by 20% through focusing on live-seafood offering. Launched a calendar of lifestyle events in the fine-dining restaurants for loyal gaming patrons. Part of a core-team that implemented Kaizen that dramatically improved operating efficiency, quality and employee engagement – a concept later replicated across the organization and adopted by most major Casino resorts in Macau.", "experiences/5/jobEndedOn": "5-2017", "experiences/5/jobLocation": "Macau", "experiences/5/jobStartedOn": "7-2012", "experiences/5/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/5/title": "Director of Food and Beverage, Sands Macau", "experiences/6/companyName": "Sands Macau", "experiences/6/jobDescription": "Managed the Food and Beverage service operation consisting of 5 restaurants, entertainment lounge, casino beverage service, banquet operations, in-room dining, pool-side services and Team dining through 12 outlet managers and 450 employees. Developed staff training solutions to deliver exceptional and competitive service in a highly competitive environment, resulting in revenues and profitability that exceeded company objectives. Drove change management and worked with the culinary team to create new value propositions that aligned with property repositioning. Strong focus on gaming F&B services with new programs such as beverage on demand and improved operational efficiencies.", "experie