 room nights and $80,000 2009\nDrove food and beverage national contracts and negotiation for the New Zealand region for all 8 hotels", "experiences/10/jobEndedOn": "11-2009", "experiences/10/jobStartedOn": "7-2008", "experiences/10/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/10/title": "Food and Beverage Operations Manager", "experiences/11/companyName": "Holiday Inn Wellington", "experiences/11/jobDescription": "Opening the newest and largest hotel in Wellington at the time, this hotel was an immediate success and I worked very closely with the F&amp;B Manager to design the Food and Beverage operation and product. First 12 Months was responsible for Minibar, Room Service and Restaurant, 6 months Conference Operations Manager.\nResponsible for many of the below tasks as mentioned in previous roles, my success with the hotel was producing an extremely profitable department with a finishing result of 35% flow down to the bottom line for the first year of operation. We had strong reviews for Plate Restaurant in the first year and we had built up a strong local base of business. I was involved in designing all aspects of the business including web design and had full control of the P&amp;L which was owned by the developer of the property. I did a 6 week secondment at the Holiday Inn on Esplanade Darwin where in just a small amount of time I reopened and rebranded the restaurant, updated the wine list, redesigned the till system and assisted in Banquet operations and beverage updating\n\nAs Conference Operations Manager at the HIW my P&amp;L regularly presented a 40 -45% net profit, I updated procedures and worked on quality within the department leaving a high level of service, great product and highly profitable operation. \n\nAt this hotel, both of my 2IC's were trained and promoted into my vacant position with great success", "experiences/11/jobEndedOn": "6-2008", "experiences/11/jobStartedOn": "1-2006", "experiences/11/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/11/title":